content.text:
TITLE: Configure Agent with Tools and maxSteps for Multi-step Operations (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to define an agent with a tool (a calculator) and configure the `maxSteps` parameter to allow the agent to perform multiple sequential LLM calls, especially when using tools. It shows agent initialization, tool definition, and a `generate` call with `maxSteps`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/docs/agents/overview.mdx#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";
import { openai } from "@ai-sdk/openai";
import * as mathjs from "mathjs";
import { z } from "zod";

export const myAgent = new Agent({
  name: "My Agent",
  instructions: "You are a helpful assistant that can solve math problems.",
  model: openai("gpt-4o-mini"),
  tools: {
    calculate: {
      description: "Calculator for mathematical expressions",
      schema: z.object({ expression: z.string() }),
      execute: async ({ expression }) => mathjs.evaluate(expression),
    },
  },
});

const response = await myAgent.generate(
  [
    {
      role: "user",
      content:
        "If a taxi driver earns $9461 per hour and works 12 hours a day, how much do they earn in one day?",
    },
  ],
  {
    maxSteps: 5, // Allow up to 5 tool usage steps
  },
);
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Initialize Mastra Project with Specific Components and LLM
DESCRIPTION: Create a new Mastra project using npx, specifying a comma-separated list of components (agents, tools) and setting Anthropic as the default LLM provider.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/packages/create-mastra/README.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
npx create-mastra@latest -c agents,tools -l anthropic
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Add a Custom Tool to a Mastra Agent
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet shows how to integrate a previously defined tool (like `weatherInfo`) into a Mastra agent's configuration. The tool is added to the `tools` property of the `Agent` constructor, making it available for the agent to use based on its instructions and the user's prompt.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/docs/agents/using-tools-and-mcp.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";
import { openai } from "@ai-sdk/openai";
import { weatherInfo } from "../tools/weatherInfo";

export const weatherAgent = new Agent({
  name: "Weather Agent",
  instructions:
    "You are a helpful assistant that provides current weather information. When asked about the weather, use the weather information tool to fetch the data.",
  model: openai("gpt-4o-mini"),
  tools: {
    weatherInfo,
  },
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configure MCPServer to Expose a Mastra Agent as a Tool
DESCRIPTION: This configuration snippet demonstrates how to initialize an `MCPServer` and expose a Mastra `Agent` as a callable tool. The agent is automatically converted, named `ask_<agentKey>`, and its `description` property is used for the tool's description, enabling other AI models or MCP clients to interact with it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/docs/agents/using-tools-and-mcp.mdx#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";
import { MCPServer } from "@mastra/mcp";
import { openai } from "@ai-sdk/openai";
import { weatherInfo } from "../tools/weatherInfo";
import { generalHelper } from "../agents/generalHelper";

const server = new MCPServer({
  name: "My Custom Server with Agent-Tool",
  version: "1.0.0",
  tools: {
    weatherInfo,
  },
  agents: { generalHelper }, // Exposes 'ask_generalHelper' tool
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Filter Tool Calls from Memory Messages
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the `ToolCallFilter` processor to remove tool calls and their results from memory messages before they are sent to the LLM. This helps save tokens and can prevent the agent from relying on previous tool results. Examples include removing all tool calls or excluding specific ones, with `TokenLimiter` placed last for optimal performance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/docs/memory/memory-processors.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Memory } from "@mastra/memory";
import { ToolCallFilter, TokenLimiter } from "@mastra/memory/processors";

const memoryFilteringTools = new Memory({
  processors: [
    // Example 1: Remove all tool calls/results
    new ToolCallFilter(),

    // Example 2: Remove only noisy image generation tool calls/results
    new ToolCallFilter({ exclude: ["generateImageTool"] }),

    // Always place TokenLimiter last
    new TokenLimiter(127000),
  ],
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Integrate MCP Server Tools into a Mastra Agent
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet demonstrates how to make tools from connected MCP servers available to a Mastra agent. It uses the `mcp.getTools()` method to asynchronously fetch tools from the configured `MCPClient` and assigns them to the agent's `tools` property, allowing the agent to leverage external capabilities.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/docs/agents/using-tools-and-mcp.mdx#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";
import { openai } from "@ai-sdk/openai";
import { mcp } from "../mcp";

// Create an agent and add tools from the MCP client
const agent = new Agent({
  name: "Agent with MCP Tools",
  instructions: "You can use tools from connected MCP servers.",
  model: openai("gpt-4o-mini"),
  tools: await mcp.getTools(),
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Create Mastra Agent with Mixed Tool Formats
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript example demonstrates how to create a Mastra `Agent` that integrates tools defined using both Mastra's `createTool` and the Vercel AI SDK's `tool` format. It shows how to configure the agent with different tool instances.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/docs/tools-mcp/advanced-usage.mdx#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";
import { openai } from "@ai-sdk/openai";
import { vercelWeatherTool } from "../tools/vercelWeatherTool"; // Vercel AI SDK tool
import { mastraTool } from "../tools/mastraTool"; // Mastra createTool tool

export const mixedToolsAgent = new Agent({
  name: "Mixed Tools Agent",
  instructions: "You can use tools defined in different formats.",
  model: openai("gpt-4o-mini"),
  tools: {
    weatherVercel: vercelWeatherTool,
    someMastraTool: mastraTool,
  },
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Example: Passing Tools to Agent
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to pass the namespaced tools obtained from `mcp.getTools()` to an Agent constructor, integrating them for use in an agent definition.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/reference/tools/mcp-client.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
new Agent({ tools: await mcp.getTools() });
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Define a Mastra Agent with OpenAI for Fact Generation
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript example demonstrates how to define a Mastra Agent that uses OpenAI's GPT-4o model. The agent is configured with a name, description, and instructions to generate facts about a country based on a city input, showcasing a common pattern for LLM integration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/docs/workflows/using-with-agents-and-tools.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { openai } from "@ai-sdk/openai";
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";

export const testAgent = new Agent({
  name: "test-agent",
  description: "Create facts for a country based on the city",
  instructions: `Return an interesting fact about the country based on the city provided`,
  model: openai("gpt-4o")
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Example: Passing Toolsets to Agent Stream
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to dynamically pass tool implementations obtained from `mcp.getToolsets()` to an agent's `stream` method, enabling on-the-fly tool resolution.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/reference/tools/mcp-client.mdx#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const res = await agent.stream(prompt, {
  toolsets: await mcp.getToolsets()
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Define and Use Client-Side Tools with Agents
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to define a custom client-side tool using `createTool` with `zod` for input schema validation. It then demonstrates how to register and use this tool with both `agent.generate` and `agent.stream` methods, showing how to handle tool call parts in the streamed response.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/reference/client-js/agents.mdx#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createTool } from '@mastra/core/tools';
import { z } from 'zod';

const colorChangeTool = createTool({
  id: 'changeColor',
  description: 'Changes the background color',
  inputSchema: z.object({
    color: z.string()
  }),
  execute: async ({ context }) => {
    document.body.style.backgroundColor = context.color;
    return { success: true };
  }
});


// Use with generate
const response = await agent.generate({
  messages: 'Change the background to blue',
  clientTools: {colorChangeTool}
});

// Use with stream
const response = await agent.stream({
  messages: 'Change the background to green',
  clientTools: {colorChangeTool}
});

response.processDataStream({
  onTextPart: (text) => console.log(text),
  onToolCallPart: (toolCall) => console.log('Tool called:', toolCall.toolName)
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Add a Custom Tool to an Agent's Configuration
DESCRIPTION: This code block shows how to add the imported 'getTransactionsTool' to the 'financialAgent' configuration. It involves updating the agent's 'tools' property and also updating the 'instructions' to inform the agent about the new tool's purpose and usage.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/course/01-first-agent/12-connecting-tool-to-agent.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export const financialAgent = new Agent({
  name: "Financial Assistant Agent",
  instructions: `ROLE DEFINITION
  // ... existing instructions ...

  TOOLS
  - Use the getTransactions tool to fetch financial transaction data.
  - Analyze the transaction data to answer user questions about their spending.`,
  model: openai("gpt-4o"),
  tools: { getTransactionsTool } 
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configure Agent with Static Tools using getTools()
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use `mcp.getTools()` to fetch all tools from configured servers and pass them to the `Agent` constructor for static tool configuration, suitable for single-user or fixed setups.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/docs/tools-mcp/mcp-overview.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";
// ... mcp client setup

const agent = new Agent({
  // ... other agent config
  tools: await mcp.getTools(),
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Retrieve Information About an Agent Tool
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to fetch details about a specific tool that an agent is configured to use, identified by its tool ID.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/reference/client-js/agents.mdx#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const tool = await agent.getTool("tool-id");
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Install Mastra MCP Package
DESCRIPTION: This command-line snippet provides the installation instruction for the `@mastra/mcp` package using npm. This package is necessary to connect Mastra agents to Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers and utilize external tools and resources.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/docs/agents/using-tools-and-mcp.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
npm install @mastra/mcp@latest
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Utilize MCPClient Configured Toolsets with Agents
DESCRIPTION: Shows how the `MCPClient` can provide configured toolsets, which can then be passed to an LLM or agent for use. This integrates the validated MCP configurations directly into agent workflows.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/explorations/mcp-registry-client/README.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
const toolsets = await configuration.getConnectedTools()

const res = await agent.generate(prompt, {
	toolsets,
})
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Create a Custom Agent Tool
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to create a custom tool using `createTool` from `@mastra/core/tools`. Tools allow agents to interact with external systems. Each tool requires an ID, an input schema for validation, a description, and an `execute` function for its implementation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/packages/core/README.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { createTool } from '@mastra/core/tools';
import { z } from 'zod';

const weatherInfo = createTool({
  id: 'Get Weather Information',
  inputSchema: z.object({
    city: z.string(),
  }),
  description: 'Fetches the current weather information for a given city',
  execute: async ({ context: { city } }) => {
    // Tool implementation
  },
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Import a Custom Tool into an Agent File
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to import a custom tool, specifically 'getTransactionsTool', into an agent's TypeScript file. This is the first step to make the tool accessible to the agent.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/course/01-first-agent/12-connecting-tool-to-agent.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { getTransactionsTool } from "../tools/get-transactions-tool";
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Configure Agent Instructions with Gmail Tools
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code snippet demonstrates how to update an agent's instructions to include details about available tools, specifically Gmail. By embedding tool descriptions directly into the agent's instructions, the agent gains crucial context on when and how to utilize these tools, enhancing its ability to respond effectively to user requests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/course/02-agent-tools-mcp/10-updating-agent-instructions-zapier.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export const personalAssistantAgent = new Agent({
