TITLE: MCPServer Agent-to-Tool Conversion API
DESCRIPTION: Details the automatic conversion of Mastra Agents into callable tools by `MCPServer`. Explains tool naming (`ask_<agentKey>`), functionality (description, input, execution, output), and precedence rules for name collisions. Emphasizes the requirement for agents to have a non-empty `description` property for successful conversion.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mastra-ai/mastra/blob/main/docs/src/content/en/reference/tools/mcp-server.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: APIDOC
CODE:
```
MCPServer Agent-to-Tool Conversion:
  Purpose: Automatically exposes Mastra Agents as callable tools.

  Configuration Property:
    agents: object
      Description: A dictionary where keys are agent identifiers and values are Agent instances.

  Generated Tool Structure:
    Tool Name: ask_<agentKey>
      Description: "Ask agent <AgentName> a question. Original agent instructions: <agent description>"
      Input:
        type: object
        properties:
          message:
            type: string
            description: "Your question for the agent"
      Execution: Invokes agent.generate(query) with the 'message' input.
      Output: Direct result from agent.generate() method.

  Constraints & Precedence:
    Agent Description Requirement:
      Agents must have a non-empty 'description' string property set during instantiation.
      Example: new Agent({ name: 'myAgent', description: 'This agent does X.' })
      Failure to meet this requirement will cause MCPServer instantiation to fail.
    Name Collisions:
      If an explicit tool (defined in 'tools' config) has the same name as an agent-derived tool, the explicit tool takes precedence.
      The agent will not be converted to a tool in this case, and a warning will be logged.
```

